Crate root for `ctx-core`; contains no logic itself, only re-exports the two shared submodules, `access` and `hashtree`.

These modules exist here specifically so multiple tools (`ctx-scan`, `ctx-context`) consume one canonical copy rather than each maintaining its own: `access` is the single source of truth for the secret/binary denylist (per DECISIONS ADR-023 — a divergent copy is treated as a secret-exfiltration bug), and `hashtree` defines the content-hash sidecar schema shared between the generator and the chain server so hashes recorded by one are comparable by the other. Each consuming crate is expected to map these modules' neutral results into its own typed error — this crate does not define a crate-wide error type.

No public functions are declared directly in this file; all behavior lives in the two submodules.